c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume brings together sixteen in-depth studies of final particles in various languages of the world, offering a rich variety of approaches to this still relatively underresearched class of elements. The volume is of interest to typologists, to experts in syntax and the analysis of spoken language, and to linguists studying the form and function of final particles in single languages. Final particles offers an overview of the different types of final particles found in typologically distinct languages, different methological approaches to the study of final particles, and of typical grammaticalization pathways that these elements have taken in different languages.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxParticles. 0aLanguage and languagesxGrammars. 4aDiscourse Particles. 4aFinal Particles. 4aRelationship Between Language and Context. 4aRight Periphery. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aHancil, Sylvie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHaselow, Alexander, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPost, Margje, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103941840 cprintz978311035380840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311037557240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110375572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110375572.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_